Class Check

  • java.lang.Object
    • classes.Check

  • public class Check
extends java.lang.Object
    Check class represents one check made on a particular website at a precise date

    One check is characterized by :

    • A unique id
    • The HTTP Status Code returned by the header when checking the website
    • The response time in milliseconds
    • The id of the Website on which the check is made
    • The date when the check is made

    Author:
    gabriellerappaport

      • Check

        public Check(java.lang.Integer idCheck,
             java.lang.Integer httpStatusCode,
             long responseTime,
             java.lang.Integer idWebsite,
             java.util.Date date)
        First Constructor for a check.

        This first method is useful when we retrieve a check stored in the database. In fact, we can set the idCheck and the date because they are stored in the database.

        Parameters:
        idCheck - Unique Id of the check
        httpStatusCode - HTTP Status Code of the check
        responseTime - Response Time of the check
        idWebsite - Id of the website the check is made on
        date - Date of the check
        See Also:
        CheckDao

      • Check

        public Check(java.lang.Integer httpStatusCode,
             long responseTime,
             java.lang.Integer idWebsite)
        Second Constructor for a check.

        This second method is useful when we create a check in the MonitorCheck class. In fact, the idCheck and date will be generated when the check is stored in the database. Thus, we don't have the informations yet.

        Parameters:
        httpStatusCode - HTTP Status Code of the check
        responseTime - Response Time of the check
        idWebsite - Id of the website the check is made on
        See Also:
        MonitorCheck
